ISLAMABAD, Aug 28 (APP): The ongoing internet slowdown across the country is mainly due to a fault in two (SMW4, AAE-1) of the seven international submarine cables connecting Pakistan internationally.
According to a news release issued by the Pakistan Telecommunication Authority (PTA) on Wednesday, The fault in the SMW-4 submarine cable is likely to be repaired by early October 2024. Whereas submarine cable AAE-1 has been repaired this may improve internet experience.‚Äù
